Author::::SteB1
DateTime::::2016-03-08T16:13:52Z
This is a very good idea. There is potentially great benefit for biodiversity from vegetation around these solar farms, which can potentially be similar to species rich grass meadows of the past. By 1984 we'd lost an incredible 97% of our species rich grassland since the WW2 because of the intensification of agriculture. This meant massive declines in the birds, insects and plants which relied on these habitats. Most farmland is intensively farmed to produce as much yield and profit as possible, so we need to create as much of this type of habitat in the countryside as is possible.http://www.lancswt.org.uk/south-pennines-grasslands



